column1:
"We are closed until August 18th due to prior
engagements"?
Welp, sure didn't see that one coming.

Ooh, now there's an idea! Let's get into some
Phantom Thieves action in the real world!

Oh, yeah! If no one's really here, then we
could investigate all we wanted once we
infiltrated the place.

But leaving empty-handed's no good... You
know, we could always just sneak in...

Hey, nothing that lands you in jail. Criminal
trespassing'll cop you a felony.

Plus, any evidence gained through a criminal
act is impermissible in court. That'd make this
whole trip pointless.

The sign says the 18th, so we'll just wait till
tomorrow. Easier, and less illegal.

Once the staff is back, I can start flashing my
badge and asking questions.

This place is all kinds of shady, so I'm sure I'll
turn up plenty of dirt with enough pokin'
around.

Once I've got some evidence, I can announce
the start of an official investigation, and at that
point we confiscate whatever we need.
I see. That's quite the tactical approach.

Whoa, check out the skills of Zenkichi:
Private Eye!

If we're waiting until tomorrow, that gives us
quite some time.

Wait, you mean... we get to party all day on the
beach!?

Yeah, we don't want to waste any more time!
How often do we get a chance like this?
Come on now... We are on a case, you know.
He's right. We are on a case, you know.
Actually, that's not the worst idea.

Getting too nosy right away could get people
suspicious, and we cannot have that.

We'd be better off trying to lay low around
the tourists for now.
And to top it off—a barbecue!?

We have a winner! Let's round up the supplies
before we venture forth!

Or rather, nearby store. The only supermarket
on the island is back at the port.

We returned to the port and
completed our shopping...
